{{Quote|The man in charge, Prefect Talmont, seems to spend most of his time trying to get himself reassigned, ignoring the blatant crime in the streets of Mos Eisley.|[[Mammon Hoole]]|<ref name="The Illustrated Star Wars Universe">''[[The Illustrated Star Wars Universe]]''</ref>}}
'''Eugene Talmont''' was the [[Imperial Prefect]] of [[Mos Eisley/Legends|Mos Eisley]] spaceport. Following in the footsteps of his father, he was constantly assigned to backwater worlds and cities, due to his unremarkable past. When given his Mos Eisley assignment, he at first saw it as an opportunity to reform and tame the lowlifes and riffraff that populated the streets, but in a short time, he began dedicating all his resources to obtaining a transfer.

At first setting his sights on [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel]] fugitives who wandered into his territory, Talmont began combating the [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt]] cartels that harried honest business in Mos Eisley. He had no qualms about taking bribes and getting involved in underhanded business to fight [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba Desilijic Tiure]], the most powerful crime lord in the sector. At first hiring honest [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] citizens to infiltrate Jabba's community, Talmont's actions drew the attention of [[Governor/Legends|Governor]] [[Tour Aryon]], who contacted the [[Imperial Security Bureau/Legends|Imperial Security Bureau]], [[Imperial Intelligence/Legends|Imperial Intelligence]], and the [[Inquisitorius/Legends|Inquisitorius]] in turn to discover the truth behind the Prefect's dealings. Talmont was able to evade disaster, though, and by [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]] he was still working to destroy Jabba's empire.

==Biography==
===Assignment===
{{Quote|I see! They think they can get away with it, but they have yet to deal with Prefect Talmont!|Prefect Eugene Talmont|<ref name="gg7" />}}
Eugene Talmont served the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] loyally, like his father, but his untarnished reputation and low-key background led him to be transferred from unremarkable post to unremarkable post. He began to develop a grudge against his father, considering him to be an inferior [[Human/Legends|human being]]. In [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]], he found himself at [[Mos Eisley/Legends|Mos Eisley]], a [[Spaceport/Legends|spaceport]] on the arid [[Planet/Legends|planet]] of [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]], where he was to serve as [[Prefect/Legends|Prefect]]. Upon learning that his predecessor, [[Orun Depp]], had been assassinated by [[IG-72]], he devised a series of schemes to get himself transferred. At first, Talmont saw the job as an opportunity to tame the barbaric nature of Tatooine's denizens, but after a while, he began to suspect that someone in the upper echelons of the government disliked him.<ref name="gg7" /><ref name="m5">''[[Star Wars Missions 5: The Hunt for Han Solo]]''</ref> A civilian officer, Talmont had a squad of [[Stormtrooper/Legends|Stormtroopers]] at his disposal, but he was required to make formal requests of [[Lieutenant/Legends|Lieutenant]] [[Harburik]], the squad leader. He was assigned to work out of Mos Eisley's dingy regional offices, where he would meet employees and citizens alike.<ref name="sot">''[[Secrets of Tatooine]]''</ref>

One of Talmont's other employees was the spy [[Garindan/Legends|Garindan]].<ref name="ff">{{FactFile|11|GAR 1-4|Garindan}}</ref> At some stage, Garindan, working with the [[Devaronian/Legends|Devaronian]] [[Kardue'sai'Malloc/Legends|Labria]], was able to learn that a group of spacers were planning to break the smuggler [[Big Bunji/Legends|Big Bunji]] out of Imperial custody, as Bunji himself was being delivered to Mos Eisley aboard a [[Speeder truck/Legends|hover truck]]. Talmont, in response, set up a trap, and had the hover truck filled with stormtroopers, while Bunji was clandestinely delivered to [[Docking Bay 87 (Mos Eisley)|Docking Bay 87]]. The stormtroopers, as expected, engaged the spacers, but they were able to break free, track down Bunji, and free him anyway.<ref name="tmasblac">{{WEGCite|book=Mos Eisley Adventure Set|story=There's Many a Slip Betwixt Cup and Lip}}</ref>

===The hunt for Han Solo===
{{Quote|You will get your reward, and I will get sent to a post on a far, far better world. You have my word on that. My solemn word.|Prefect Eugene Talmont|<ref name="m5" />}}
Within the year, Talmont's power began to rival that of [[Governor/Legends|Governor]] [[Tour Aryon]], and he had a degree of jurisdiction over the entire planet. Still, he sought to be transferred, and came up with a plan to impress his superiors. [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]], captain of the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']], was wanted by the Empire, and Talmont's men had gained intelligence that he would be returning to Tatooine to pay off [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba Desilijic Tiure]], a crime lord who had a bounty on the fugitive [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggler's]] head. Hiring three [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunters]], [[Dengar/Legends|Dengar]], [[Udin]], and [[Eron Stonefield]], Talmont intended to have his employees camp outside [[Jabba's Palace/Legends|Jabba's Palace]] and wait for Solo to arrive. Talmont promised to pay the bounty hunters considerably, and believed that the capture of such an elusive terrorist would secure his passage to a better post.<ref name="m5" />

What was essentially a simple plan, however, evolved into a complex, [[The galaxy/Legends|galaxy]]-wide chase involving kidnappings of [[Hutt/Legends|Hutts]],<ref name="m5" /> planetary revolutions,<ref name="m7">''[[Star Wars Missions 7: Ithorian Invasion]]''</ref> and trade disputes.<ref name="m6">''[[Star Wars Missions 6: The Search for Grubba the Hutt]]''</ref> With his [[Huttese/Legends#People|Ur-Damo]] in the clutches of Solo, Jabba expressed interest in the hunt, and contacted Talmont. Though the Prefect was no friend of the Hutt, he assured him that the three hunters were totally capable. With the Hutt now involved, Talmont's involvement diminished. Though the hunters eventually caught Solo, they unwittingly handed them over to [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebels]], disguised as Imperials. As a result, celebrations broke out across Mos Eisley, and Talmont did not get the transfer he sought.<ref name="m8">''[[Star Wars Missions 8: Togorian Trap]]''</ref><ref name="swg">{{GalaxiesAED}}</ref>

===Reporting on the Hutt ''kajidics''===
{{Quote|The Hutts, unsurprisingly, think themselves superior to all other creatures in the galaxy, including humanoids. Further, the mere existence of these gangsters promotes immorality.|Excerpt from Prefect Eugene Talmont's report to ISB|<ref name="uw">{{InsiderCite|89|Underworld: A Galaxy of Scum and Villainy}}</ref>}}
Within the same year, Prefect Talmont was called upon by the [[Imperial Security Bureau/Legends|Imperial Security Bureau]] (ISB) to research the [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt]] [[Kajidic/Legends|''kajidics'']], or clans. Talmont did so, and compiled a particularly critical and damning report of the ''kajidics'', mentioning such psychological theories as "[[The Hutt Mirror]]." Talmont's report was dispatched to the ISB, and in turn, [[Commander/Legends|Commander]] [[Maximillian Seerdon]] sent it to [[Grand Vizier/Legends|Grand Vizier]] [[Sate Pestage/Legends|Sate Pestage]].<ref name="uw" />

===Operations in Bestine===
[[File:EugeneTalmont.png|thumb|left|200px|Prefect Talmont during his stay in Bestine]]
{{Quote|Your services has been invaluable to me and the greater good of the Empire. It's a sad time when wearing the Prefect's uniform is to wrap oneself in thorns and razorwire. Go, I am distraught.|Prefect Eugene Talmont|<ref name="swg" />}}
In [[1 ABY/Legends|1 ABY]], [[Wilhalm Skrim]], Governor Aryon's secretary, referred a traveling Imperial [[Spacer/Legends|spacer]] onto Talmont. Talmont, who was visiting [[Bestine (city)/Legends|Bestine]], had several errands that the spacer was willing to run. First, he sent the spacer to kill the gangster [[Akkar Plint]], who was working for [[Gohn Bimmin]], an Imperial official. Bimmin had apparently fabricated evidence claiming that Talmont was involved in a bribery scandal, and was heading to Bestine to present his case. The spacer fulfilled the task, and Talmont was safe, for the moment. He then sent the spacer to assassinate Bimmin, further securing the safety of the Prefecture from harmful allegations.<ref name="swg" />

Impressed with the spacer's work, Talmont enlisted the nomad in his war against the Hutts. He sent the spacer on another assassination mission, this time to kill the Hutt employee [[Snrrrlagga]]. The spacer succeeded, and Talmont grew confident that he would gain the upper hand in the minor conflict. Governor Aryon grew suspicious of Talmont's movements, however, and enlisted the services of an Imperial Security Bureau officer to keep an eye on the Prefect. Talmont, indignant, discovered that the [[Bothan/Legends|Bothan]] spy [[Nwilla Thar'lyat]] had been providing the ISB officer with details on his operations, and so sent the spacer to kill Thar'lyat.<ref name="swg" />

Though Thar'lyat perished, Aryon did not give up, and with the ISB's effectiveness hampered, enlisted [[Imperial Intelligence/Legends|Imperial Intelligence]] to do the job. Talmont was confident he could deal with the Intelligence officer, but knew that the officer's guard, [[Klaua Jik]], would pose a problem. Reminding the spacer to be exceptionally secretive, Talmont enlisted them, once again, for an assassination task, with Jik as the target. Jik, shortly thereafter, perished, and Talmont found himself able to move freely again. Still, Aryon was not satisfied. She called upon the [[Inquisitorius/Legends|Inquisitorius]], who sent one of their number to interrogate those close to Talmont. The Prefect, panicking, dispatched the spacer to kill [[Harbo Linn]], a member of the Prefecture who would reveal damning information if he were to fall into the hands of the Inquisitor. The spacer succeeded, but Talmont was too distraught to be pleased.<ref name="swg" />

===Plotting to remove Jabba===
Talmont realized he had to get rid of Jabba and his criminal enterprises that riddled Mos Eisley. At first, he hired Imperial agents to infiltrate [[Jabba's Palace/Legends|Jabba's Palace]] and steal data discs containing information about the crime lord's bribery of important officials.<ref name="wwg">{{InsiderCite|65|Who's Who in Star Wars Galaxies|Who's Who in ''Star Wars'' Galaxies}}</ref> He continued in his efforts, but instead of hampering the crime lord's movements, he simply created a set of easily avoided obstacles.<ref name="sot" /> Further setbacks occurred with the hiring of [[Dannik Jerriko]], an [[Anzat (species)|Anzati]] assassin. Jerriko was in both Talmont and Lady Valarian's employ, causing the Prefect a great deal of grief and confusion.<ref name="tfjpbf">{{StoryCite|story=Of the Day's Annoyances: Bib Fortuna's Tale|book=Tales from Jabba's Palace}}</ref> In [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]], he contacted two members of Jabba's cartel: [[Tessek/Legends|Tessek]] and [[Ree-Yees/Legends|Ree-Yees]]. Ree-Yees, an alcoholic murderer from [[Kinyen/Legends|Kinyen]], had three deaths on his record, but Talmont agreed to clear the [[Gran/Legends|Gran's]] name if he could eliminate Jabba. As such, he had his men deliver the parts of a bomb gradually to Ree-Yees, in the hope that the Gran would assemble it and eliminate Jabba.<ref name="tfjpgg">{{StoryCite|story=Goatgrass: The Tale of Ree-Yees|book=Tales from Jabba's Palace}}</ref>

Tessek, Jabba's accountant, made a separate deal with Talmont. He would arrange to have Jabba inspect a [[Spice/Legends|spice]] shipment in a large warehouse in Mos Eisley, during which Talmont and his men would raid the illegal stash and arrest the Hutt. Talmont believed that by eliminating Jabba, either way, he would be transferred to another world.<ref name="tfjpts">{{StoryCite|story=A Free Quarren in the Palace: Tessek's Tale|book=Tales from Jabba's Palace}}</ref> The day before the planned raid, Talmont went to the [[Lucky Despot]] with several of his men, and was met by [[Ephant Mon/Legends|Ephant Mon]], another of Jabba's employees. Watching the [[Chevin/Legends|Chevin]] dispatch a pair of local thugs, he commended Mon on his combat skills. Mon, however, hinted that he knew of Tessek's plan, causing Talmont to fret.<ref name="tfjpep">{{StoryCite|story=Old Friends: Ephant Mon's Tale|book=Tales from Jabba's Palace}}</ref> Luckily for Talmont, Jabba was assassinated by [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]] the following day at the Pit of Carkoon.<ref name="rotj">{{Film|VI}}</ref>

The Prefect was also working with swoop gangs in order to incite chaos in Mos Eisley, allowing him to declare martial law and consolidate his power. A [[Imperial Customs Corvette|light corvette]] arrived and told him about the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]]. However, when his plot came to light he was forced to flee.<ref name="Passage From Perdition">{{WEGCite|story=The Passage From Perdition|book=Mos Eisley Adventure Set}}</ref>

==Personality and traits==
{{Quote|Oh, this is a hideous world.|Prefect Eugene Talmont|<ref name="m5" />}}
Eugene Talmont was a rather bitter man, particularly towards his father and his superiors. His father had, in Talmont's opinion, always been given choice assignments and postings, while he himself had received nothing but backwater posts. Adding insult to injury, Talmont believed himself to be a far better man than his father. The Prefect did not put his posting to Tatooine down to coincidence, either, as he was convinced that his superiors had given him a poor assignment just to spite him. While at first Talmont thought Mos Eisley may provide him with an opportunity to subdue the rowdy citizens, he quickly discovered that it was a highly dangerous and barren city, with practically no prospects for advancement.<ref name="m5" /> He apparently also had a vicious temper when learning of failures from within his unit, as the colonel in charge of what was the [[Tusken Bunker]] hired a spacer to clear out the [[Tusken Raider/Legends|Tusken Raiders]] who had taken over the base over reporting the loss due to fearing being reprimanded by him.<ref name="swg" />

He had no qualms with taking bribes,<ref name="gg7" /> but was utterly disgusted at the fact that he was accused of misconduct. He frequently clashed with the governor, and usually tried to avoid her, but when Talmont's assassination orders got out of hand, the governor began to investigate. Talmont panicked in such an instance, and simply ordered more killings, which did, eventually, resolve the problem.<ref name="swg" /> He believed that accepting bribes was perfectly normal for a man in his position, and accepted credits from almost every business in Mos Eisley, in exchange for a selectively blind eye.<ref name="sot" /> Talmont's objective became not so much "fixing" Mos Eisley, but doing something noteworthy to attract the attention of his superiors, as he hated Tatooine and sought a transfer. He concocted a wide variety of schemes, none of which succeeded.<ref name="m5" /><ref name="tfjpgg" />

A slight man of wiry build, Talmont was not a particularly imposing figure, and was also physically short-sighted. In his first year at Mos Eisley, he wore a toupee, but substituted it in 1 ABY for an officer's cap, to match his prefect's uniform. He had a walking stick as well, but he had seemingly done away with it by the time of his second year on the job.<ref name="swg" /><ref name="m5" /><ref name="gg7" />

==Behind the scenes==
Eugene Talmont was created by [[Martin Wixted]] and first appeared in the [[West End Games]] sourcebook ''[[Galaxy Guide 7: Mos Eisley]]''. The character went on to appear in the short-story collection ''[[Tales from Jabba's Palace]]'', and made his first in-story appearance in [[Kenneth C. Flint]]'s ''[[Old Friends: Ephant Mon's Tale]]''. The character was later used by [[Dave Wolverton]], as the catalyst for the plot of the second arc of the ''[[Star Wars Missions]]'' series, in [[1998]].

In the ''[[Star Wars Miniatures Battles]]'' scenario ''[[A Line in the Sand...]]'', which occurs during the [[Rebellion on Tatooine]], Prefect Talmont can be rescued by the Empire, captured by the Mos Eisley militia, or killed by the swoop gang.

